					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-750512#post-1924500</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-750512/lana-neal-sings-the-blues#post-1924500</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 29 Dec 2013 20:51:42 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>anqxyr</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>966960</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>So, I read this today not knowing what it was about, then read 1229 for the first time. I no-voted both. Noir is not my kind of thing, and the original article didn't really creep me out or otherwise made me feel.</p> <p>Then I kept thinking about this. About how intimate the clip's message was in this tale and how it affected the protagonist. About the other videos. About the missing children, and their last observed location. About who might have seen those children last. Urgh. Take your upvotes, both of them.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
