					<![CDATA[
						 <p>You write Noir like it should be written, without the need of cliche and ancient by-gones that most authors cling to, thinking that the genre lies in there somewhere. I read this in the voice of Tom Waits on a bad day, and my mouth still tastes like bourbon.</p> <p>+1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
